The Visual Experience Database (VED) is a database of video captured from head-mounted cameras, complete with recordings of the videographers eye movements taken by a diverse set of observers engaged in common, everyday activities such as shopping, eating, or walking. By creating a database that represents common, human experiences, we bypass the many biases of extant datasets, with the aim of increasing the efficacy of computer vision algorithms.

The creation of the VED is supported by an EPSCoR Research Infrastructure Improvement Program: Track-2 Focused EPSCoR Collaborations grant (award #1920896).
